<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,1008,1202]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1050,1076]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[725,749,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear shield margin, directed anteriorly, anterior lobe present; opisthosomal annuli dorsoventrally subequal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,1008,1202]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
This genus consists of 6 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,1134,1160]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
